for_developers/README.md
     1→# For developers
     3→While `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4→underlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5→flexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6→consumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7→the book or render it in a different format.
     8→
     9→The *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10→`mdbook`.
    11→
    12→The two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13→
    14→- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15→- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16→
    17→## The build process
    30→## Using `mdbook` as a library

